ense of responsibility towards the local environment. Todd extends the concept of sense of place to describe Silicon Valley as a non-place, where weakened or disrupted attachment to place threatens the environment and community. The story of the Santa Clara Valley is an American story of the development of agricultural lands and the transformation of rural regions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAgriculture and statezCaliforniazSanta Clara Valley (Santa Clara County). 0aHigh technology industriesxEnvironmental aspectszCaliforniazSanta Clara Valley (Santa Clara County). 7aHISTORY / Historical Geography.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022 Englishz978311099296008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022z9783110992939oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520389601?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520389601423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520389601/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099296-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022